'''Protein digestibility''' refers to how well a given protein is digested.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Measurement of protein digestibility in humans by a dual-tracer method|first1=Sarita |last1=Devi  |first2=Aneesia |last2=Varkey  |first3=M S |last3=Sheshshayee  |first4=Thomas |last4=Preston  |first5=Anura V |last5=Kurpad|journal=The American Journal of Clinical Nutrition|volume=107|issue=6|date= 1 June 2018}}</ref> Along with the [[amino acid score]], protein digestibility determines the values for [[PDCAAS]] and [[DIAAS]].

