{{Infobox company |name = The Writer's Block |logo = File:Storefront_of_the_Writer%27s_Block_Bookshop,_May_2015.jpg |type = [[Bookstore]] |foundation = 2014 |key_people = Scott Seeley, Drew Cohen, Chris Molnar |location = [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States |industry = [[Books]] |products = Books, periodicals, marionettes, artificial birds, anatomical models, build-your-own diorama kits |services = Literacy education, publishing | motto = | former name = |homepage = [http://www.thewritersblock.org/ thewritersblock.org] }}
'''The Writer's Block''' is an independent bookseller, publisher, and literacy educator in [[downtown Las Vegas]].
The Writer's Block was established in 2014 by [[826NYC]] co-founder Scott Seeley and Drew Cohen. It was opened with former [[826NYC|BSSco.]] store manager Chris Molnar.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thebrooklynink.com/2012/02/24/41850-wham-pow-everything-a-superhero-could-want/ |title=Wham! Pow! Everything a Superhero Could Want |publisher=Webcitation.org |accessdate=2015-05-30 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Yu2vvDih |archivedate=May 30, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.downtownproject.com/media/2015/4/28/downtown-denizen-chris-molnar |title=DOWNTOWN DENIZEN - CHRIS MOLNAR |publisher=Webcitation.org |accessdate=2015-05-30 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Yu2zsGsO |archivedate=May 30, 2015 }}</ref> It is the first independent bookstore in Las Vegas, and second in the state of [[Nevada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://knpr.org/knpr/2014-12/despite-e-books-independent-bookstore-gambling-downtown-las-vegas |title=Despite E-Books, Independent Bookstore Gambling on Downtown Las Vegas |publisher=Webcitation.org |accessdate=2015-05-30 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Yuwu7h69 |archivedate=May 30, 2015 }}</ref>
Behind the bookstore front is the literacy education component of the Writer's Block, known as Codex. Similar in layout to the educational area behind 826NYC's Superhero Supply Store,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/brooklyns-superhero-supply-co-2014-7 |title=Here's What You Can Buy At The Brooklyn Superhero Supply Co. — And How The Store Is Secretly Saving The World |publisher=Webcitation.org |accessdate=2015-05-30 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Yu3wNV2e |archivedate=May 30, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://vegasseven.com/2014/09/11/writers-block-rewriting-bookshop |title=Rewriting the Bookshop |publisher=Webcitation.org |accessdate=2015-05-30 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Yu42hw0X |archivedate=May 30, 2015 }}</ref> Codex also features movable walls, tables and desks. It is used for free writing workshops for children ages 5-18, in addition to readings, signings, and ongoing series such as [http://www.neonlit.org Neon Lit], the monthly reading by MFA and PHD writing students at [[UNLV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dtlv.com/2015/03/26/weekend-events-march-27 |title=Hawthorne Heights, Neon Lit, Chicken Shack and Remembering Aurajin |publisher=Webcitation.org |accessdate=2015-05-30 |deadurl=unfit |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Yu4DoCfD |archivedate=May 30, 2015 }}</ref>
